The evidence with the title 'Love - Wikiquote ' says Love is the expansion of two natures in such fashion that each include the other, each is enriched by the other. Love is an echo  ... Choose to love whomsoever thou wilt: all else will follow.  ... “there is much to be known,” said Adaon, “and above all much to be loved, be it the turn of the seasons or the shape of a river pebble. 
